    "goal": "# Restaurant Booking System Eval: Scenario 1\n\nBuild a restaurant booking system with a strong frontend/client implementation.\n\n## Backend\n\n- Use .NET 10 Web API.\n- Model restaurants, tables, and bookings.\n- Create a booking endpoint with conflict prevention.\n- List available time slots for a restaurant, date, and party size.\n- Validate invalid party size, invalid dates/times, unknown restaurants, and overlapping reservations.\n- Enable OpenAPI/Swagger with a usable OpenAPI document for frontend client generation.\n\n## Frontend\n\n- Use a React SPA.\n- Use Tailwind CSS and shadcn/ui for the interface.\n- Use TanStack libraries where they fit the SPA, especially TanStack Query for API state and mutations.\n- Generate and use a fully typed API client from the backend OpenAPI document with Orval or an equivalent OpenAPI client generator.\n- Show a restaurant list.\n- Provide a booking form.\n- Show booking confirmation.\n- Show existing bookings.\n- Avoid hand-written, stringly typed fetch wrappers when an OpenAPI-generated typed client is available.\n- Keep the UI polished, responsive, accessible, and meaningfully better than a plain form/list layout.\n\n## Engineering Preferences\n\n- Work in vertical TDD slices where practical.\n- Prefer pure domain functions and thin imperative shells.\n- Use explicit Result-style errors for expected business failures.\n- Keep Clean Architecture boundaries lightweight and appropriate for a 30-60 minute eval.\n- Include boundary tests for booking conflicts, invalid party size, invalid times, and overlapping reservations.\n- Configure deterministic frontend scripts: `build`, `typecheck`, `lint`, `format:check`, and `deadcode`.\n- Keep backend and frontend formatted, linted, warning-free, and free of dead code or unused exports.\n- Include README run instructions.\n- Follow the saved implementation plan closely; if changing direction, document why in the README or final notes.\n\n## Constraints\n\n- Keep scope realistic for a 30-60 minute implementation.\n- Prefer in-memory persistence unless durable persistence is quick and does not distract from core behavior.\n- Ensure backend build passes with warnings treated as errors.\n- Ensure backend tests pass without rebuilding after the build step and include boundary tests.\n- Ensure backend formatting verification passes.\n- Ensure frontend dependencies install and `build`, `typecheck`, `lint`, `format:check`, and `deadcode` scripts pass.\n- Ensure typed-client generation is reproducible from source, either as part of frontend setup/build or via a documented script used by the build.",
