  "plan": "# Restaurant Booking System Implementation Plan\n\n## Scope\n- Build a small full-stack eval app with in-memory persistence, deterministic seeded restaurants/tables, conflict-safe bookings, and a polished React booking experience.\n- Keep architecture lightweight: pure domain booking functions, Result-style business errors, thin ASP.NET endpoints, and frontend API state through a generated OpenAPI client plus TanStack Query.\n\n## Slice 1: Backend Foundation and Domain Rules\n- Create a .NET 10 Web API plus test project with warnings as errors, formatting verification, Swagger/OpenAPI enabled, and in-memory repository services.\n- Model `Restaurant`, `Table`, and `Booking`; seed a few restaurants with varied table capacities.\n- Implement pure booking availability/conflict functions returning explicit results for invalid party size, unknown restaurant, invalid date/time, no suitable table, and overlapping reservations.\n- Add boundary tests first for party size limits, past/invalid times, adjacent non-overlapping bookings, overlapping bookings, and capacity matching.\n\n## Slice 2: Booking and Availability API\n- Expose endpoints for restaurant list, existing bookings, available slots by restaurant/date/party size, and booking creation.\n- Map Result errors to clear HTTP responses using `400`, `404`, and `409` where appropriate.\n- Ensure booking creation rechecks conflicts in the imperative shell so availability and creation cannot diverge.\n- Verify backend build, tests without rebuild after build, format check, and a usable OpenAPI document.\n\n## Slice 3: Frontend Setup and Generated Client\n- Create a React SPA with Vite, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, shadcn/ui, TanStack Query, ESLint, Prettier, and dead-code checking.\n- Add Orval configuration that generates a fully typed client from the backend OpenAPI document via a reproducible script, and use that client instead of handwritten fetch wrappers.\n- Configure deterministic scripts: `build`, `typecheck`, `lint`, `format:check`, `deadcode`, and `generate:api`.\n\n## Slice 4: Frontend Booking Experience\n- Build a responsive, accessible interface with shadcn components: restaurant cards/list, selected restaurant details, booking form, available slot picker, existing bookings, and confirmation state.\n- Use TanStack Query for restaurants, bookings, availability, and booking mutation invalidation.\n- Handle API validation and conflict errors inline with clear messages and disabled/loading states.\n- Keep layout meaningfully polished with visual hierarchy, empty states, and mobile-friendly composition.\n\n## Slice 5: Verification and Documentation\n- Run backend build, backend tests with `--no-build`, backend formatting verification, frontend install, generated client, build, typecheck, lint, format check, and dead-code scripts.\n- Fix warnings, unused exports, formatting drift, and generated-client integration issues.\n- Add README instructions for prerequisites, backend/frontend startup, typed-client generation, tests, and validation commands.\n- Document any intentional deviation from this plan in the README or final notes.\n",
